## Overview

This issue tracks several important improvements planned for upcoming versions.  
The current version is functional, but there are still areas that need refinement in UI/UX, conversation management, PDF interaction, context control, and API model support.

这些问题不一定需要在同一个版本中全部完成，可以按优先级逐步拆分和实现。

---

## 1. UI Display and Layout Improvements

### Current Problems

The current UI still needs further polishing in several areas:

- Color palette is not fully consistent across pages and components.
- Some layouts may look unbalanced or visually crowded.
- Spacing, alignment, and typography need refinement.
- Different UI states, such as empty states, loading states, and error states, may not be visually consistent.
- Mobile or smaller-screen layout may still have display issues.

### Expected Improvements

- Improve overall visual consistency.
- Refine colors, spacing, typography, and layout hierarchy.
- Optimize the main interface for better readability and usability.
- Improve responsive layout behavior.
- Add or improve empty/loading/error states where necessary.

---

## 2. Conversation Tree and Document Management Improvements

### Features to Improve

- Improve the "create new conversation tree" workflow.
- Improve node deletion behavior in the conversation tree.
- Add or improve document renaming functionality on the main interface.

### Expected Behavior

- Users should be able to create new conversation trees more clearly and reliably.
- Users should be able to delete conversation nodes safely.
- Deleting a node should have predictable behavior:
  - Confirm before deletion.
  - Handle child nodes properly.
  - Avoid accidental loss of important conversation history.
- Users should be able to rename documents directly from the main interface.

### Notes

Node deletion may require further design decisions, such as:

- Whether deleting a parent node also deletes all child nodes.
- Whether deleted nodes can be restored.
- Whether the system should warn users before deleting branches.

---

## 3. Context Transmission Controls

### Current Problems

The current context transmission behavior needs more flexible user control.

### Features to Add

- Add an option to disable automatic previous-context transmission.
- Add a setting to control the length of previous context sent to the model.
- Add an option to disable automatic PDF content transmission.
- Add a feature to include context by PDF page range, such as "include previous/next N pages" or "include current page ± N pages".

### Expected Behavior

Users should be able to control what context is sent to the AI model, including:

- Whether previous conversation history is automatically included.
- How much conversation history is included.
- Whether PDF content is automatically included.
- Whether context should be selected based on PDF page position.

### Possible Settings

Examples:

- `Auto include conversation history`: on/off
- `Conversation context length`: short / medium / long / custom token limit
- `Auto include PDF context`: on/off
- `PDF context range`: current page only / current page ± 1 / current page ± N

### Goal

Improve transparency and controllability of AI interactions, especially when working with long PDFs or sensitive documents.

---

## 4. PDF Annotation and Temporary AI Interaction Annotations

### Features to Add

- Add PDF annotation editing functionality.
- Support creating, editing, and deleting annotations.
- Allow temporary PDF annotations that can be used for AI interaction without permanently changing the document.
- Allow users to select annotated content as context for AI questions.

### Expected Behavior

Users should be able to:

- Highlight or mark parts of a PDF.
- Edit existing annotations.
- Delete annotations.
- Temporarily mark PDF content for AI interaction.
- Ask AI questions based on selected or annotated PDF regions.

### Notes

There may be two types of annotations:

1. Persistent annotations  
   - Saved with the document.
   - Visible when reopening the PDF.

2. Temporary interaction annotations  
   - Used only for the current AI interaction.
   - Not necessarily saved permanently.
   - Useful for quick question-answer workflows.

---

## 5. Region-Based Conversation Feature

### Feature Description

Add a feature that allows users to select or capture a specific region of the PDF/page and start a conversation based on that selected area.

### Expected Behavior

Users should be able to:

- Select a rectangular area on the PDF.
- Use the selected region as input context for AI.
- Ask questions about the selected region.
- Optionally combine the selected region with nearby text or page context.

### Possible Use Cases

- Ask about a chart, table, formula, paragraph, or figure.
- Extract information from a selected PDF area.
- Ask AI to explain a visual or text-heavy region.
- Use selected area as temporary context for a conversation.

### Notes

This may require OCR or image-based model support depending on the selected content type.

