## 6. Public API Support Based on Custom API Model Configuration

### Current State

The system supports custom API model configuration or is planned to support it.

### Feature to Add

In addition to user-defined custom API models, provide a built-in public API option.

### Expected Behavior

Users should be able to choose between:

- Custom API provider configured by the user.
- Public/shared API provider provided by the platform.

### Possible Model Configuration Options

- Custom API base URL
- Custom API key
- Model name
- Public default model
- Public fallback model
- Provider selection

### Goal

Make the application easier to use for users who do not want to configure their own API keys, while still preserving flexibility for advanced users.

